{"generation_id":"gen_base_aflily_2bd7e648","status":"IN_QUEUE","input_text":"I remember the gentle hum of the old computer, a quiet whir beneath the joyous noise. The screen cast its flickering light, mixing with the warmer, muted glow from the room. I felt the faint scent of dust and the quiet warmth of a shared afternoon, the wood of the desk solid beneath their arms.\nThen their faces burst into view, beaming. The one with dark hair, leaning in, had his mouth wide open in a laugh, a triumphant thumbs-up. His friend, with lighter hair, mirrored the exact gesture, equally thrilled, his eyes bright on the pixelated game. Their hands almost met above the monitor, a silent, shared celebration.\nIt wasn’t just a game; it was a world they inhabited together, a moment of pure, unadulterated excitement. They were brothers in that instant, whether by blood or by bond, completely united in their joy. That connection, that easy camaraderie, was the brightest thing I held.\nI know now that these simple days of pixelated triumphs would evolve, replaced by new screens and different challenges. But this snapshot, this pure, uncomplicated happiness, would echo. It was the vibrant peak of a friendship, a feeling they’d carry long after the game was over, making this moment forever bright.","voice_id":"af_lily","voice_name":"Lily","model":"base","tokens":304,"dollar_cost":0.00304,"method":null,"audio_url":null,"error_message":null,"created_at":"2026-03-16T08:03:10.041729","started_at":null,"completed_at":null}